flowRoot.flowPara: I am a self-taught web developer with one year experience as a full time junior member of an ambitious and dynamic startup. Although I was enjoying my job, I wanted a new challenge to step up my game so I came to Denmark to study Computer Science. Now I am looking for a part-time job where I can put my knowledge into practice and get a real world feedback.
I feel best in an informal environment with emphasis on team-work, code quality and cutting-edge technologies.

go-ok is a NGO monitoring wheelchair accessibillity. I am a part of two-person team developing a browser game with Meteor and AngularJS. The goal is to gamify discovery of parking spots for disabled through Google Streetview.
eDocu is a robust web application based on dockerized microservices and the MEAN stack. My main responsibilities are development of new features using AngularJS and UI design.
Using stickers with QR code, eDocu brings the right information on the spot.
